HEADWORD: curtsy
<hw>curt"sy</hw></mhw>
<pr>(k⟦ucir⟧rt"s⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An act of civility,
respect, or reverence, made by women, consisting of a slight depression
or dropping of the body, with bending of the knees. Same as 2nd
<er>Courtesy</er>, <pos>n.</pos>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> curtsy; courtesy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

